org.paces.Stata.Input.Interfaces

Interface KeyValue

  • All Superinterfaces:
    StataVariableCreator
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    KeyValueImpl

    public interface KeyValue
extends StataVariableCreator
    Interface methods used to define methods used to handle how elements are loaded in Stata
    Version:
    0.0.0
    Author:
    Billy Buchanan

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void asKeyValue(StataTypeMap type, java.util.List<java.lang.String> keys, FlatStataJSON nodeMap)
      Method used to load all of the nodes identified by the keys param as Stata missing values; these will be cast byte values of 127 to minimize the amount of memory needed to store the missing values (this also assumes all values in the key list contain missing nodes).
      default void loadBool(java.util.List<java.lang.String> keys, FlatStataJSON nodeMap)
      Method used to load all of the nodes identified by the keys param; These are Java Booleans, but will be converted to a Stata byte type where 0 = false and 1 = true.
      default void loadDouble(java.util.List<java.lang.String> keys, FlatStataJSON nodeMap)
      Method used to load all of the nodes identified by the keys param as Stata double type values
      default void loadFloat(java.util.List<java.lang.String> keys, FlatStataJSON nodeMap)
      Method used to load all of the nodes identified by the keys param as Stata double type values; these are represented as a Float type on the JVM but will be cast to double before adding to the Stata dataset
      default void loadInt(java.util.List<java.lang.String> keys, FlatStataJSON nodeMap)
      Method used to load all of the nodes identified by the keys param as Stata int type values; these data are represented as Short types on the JVM (2-byte integers).
      default void loadLong(java.util.List<java.lang.String> keys, FlatStataJSON nodeMap)
      Method used to load all of the nodes identified by the keys param as Stata long type values; these data are represented as Integer types on the JVM (4-byte integers).

      Method used to load all of the nodes identified by the keys param as Stata missing values; these will be cast byte values of 127 to minimize the amount of memory needed to store the missing values (this also assumes all values in the key list contain missing nodes).

      Method used to load all of the nodes identified by the keys param as Stata String type values

      • loadLong

        default void loadLong(java.util.List<java.lang.String> keys,
                      FlatStataJSON nodeMap)
        Method used to load all of the nodes identified by the keys param as Stata long type values; these data are represented as Integer types on the JVM (4-byte integers). True long values are cast to Double types prior to pushing into Stata.
        Parameters:
        keys - The keys identifying the nodes to load
        nodeMap - A FlatStataJSON object
